<TITLE> Athletes leave for C'wealth Youth Games </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 9 (bdnews24.com)  An 11-member Bangladesh contingent headed by Bangladesh Olympic Association deputy general secretary Anisur Rahman Dipu left here Thursday morning for India to take part in the 3rd Commonwealth Youth Games to be held in Indian city Pune from October 12 to 18. The contingent has eight competitorstwo each for swimming, shooting, weightlifting and boxingwill vie for medals at the meet that also hosts five other disciplines of athletics, badminton, wrestling, table tennis and tennis with some 13,000 athletes competing from 71 nations. M Amzad Ali and Kazal Datta will accompany the athletes as coach-cum-managers. The BOA has announced on Thursday a 50,000 taka cash reward for those Bangladeshi athletes who would be able to bag gold medals in the third edition of the meet. The silver and bronze medalists will also be awarded by Tk 30,000 and Tk 20,000 respectively, said a BOA press release. It is the first time that Bangladesh is participating in the Commonwealth Youth Games, that started its journey in 2000 in Scotland. The last edition of the meet was held in Australia in 2004. The notable feature of the meet is that the competition venues of all sports events and the Athletes' Village are located in one single complex adjacent to the Shree Shiv Chhatrapati Stadium, according to the official website of the Games. The participants are swimmer Anik Islam (200m butterfly and 200m individual medley), swimmer Afsana Talukdar (100m & 200m freestyle), shooter Sabbir Hasan (Skeet & 10m air rifles), shooter Tripti Datta (50m rifle prone & 50m rifle 3 position), weightlifters Fayema Akhter (53kg) and Mizanur Rahman (56kg), boxers Riad Hossain (48 kg light flyweight) and Mosihur Rahman Kajal (51kg fly light flyweight). bd
